article.description: Dylan Miller scored a season-high 20 points and North Dakota State routed Division III Northland College 105-47 on Wednesday night for its 30th straight win at home.
article.headline: ND State routs Northland 105-47 for 30th home win in a row
article.linkText: ND State routs Northland 105-47 for 30th home win in a row
article.story: FARGO, N.D. -- Dylan Miller scored a season-high 20 points and North Dakota State routed Division III Northland College 105-47 on Wednesday night for its 30th straight win at home. Miller made 9 of 10 from the field and the Bison led by 58 points with 4:30 left to play. They outplayed the Lumberjacks by every measure, outrebounding them 57-18, outscoring them 74-20 in the paint, and outshooting them 59 percent to 31 percent from the field. North Dakota State's bench contributed 55 points -- more than the entire Northland squad. A.J. Jacobson and Khy Kabellis scored 16 apiece, Malik Clements added 11 and Dexter Werner 10 for the Bison (10-4) in their non-conference finale. The Bison will take on Denver in the Summit League opener on Sunday. Thomas Whiting led the Lumberjacks with 11 points.
